The United Nations General Assembly Special session on HIV/AIDS held in New York in 2001 indicated that more and more orphan households are emerging where the parent living with HIV/AIDS is the primary or sole provider of basic necessities of daily living. "Age-disparate relationships" are becoming more common. Where the male partner is much older than the female partner, there is an increased chance of the man contracting HIV and passing it to the woman.

Infecious diseases

Mainly dengue fever, filariasis, malaria, and tuberculosis are common in developing countries. In Seychelles five cases of dengue fever have been reported since 1867.[citation needed]

Contemporary

Pitfalls in Health Care Software

In some cases, healthcare software and hardware causes problems. This could be due to delivering the wrong diagnosis or due to hardware problems that could be avoided. The Ear, Nose and Throat software, for example, gave x-rays to the wrong side(s) of patients without warning users. This could happen frequently when technicians are filing patients and not verifying previously filed files. This means that patients without medical insurance, who could not afford the 3000$ per year, can't even get proper medication. The insurance company, however, has been receiving monthly deductions without ever having to deliver the medicine.
